{{Not to be confused with|November 16|qq=November 16}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月十六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 16일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}}.
== Events == * In the 2nd year of the Jōō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1654]] [[:en:January 4|January 4]]) – The excavation of the Tamagawa aqueduct was completed, with final completion in June of the following year. * In the 4th year of the Enkyō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1747]] [[:en:December 17|December 17]]) – At a performance held in Osaka at the Takemoto theater, a collaborative puppet play titled “Yoshitsune Senbon Zakura” (a production by Takeda Izumo, Miyoshi Shōraku, and Namiki Chiryū) was staged for the first time. * In the 1st year of the An'ei era / 9th year of the Meiwa era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1772]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]) – Due to ominous signs including great wind and flooding in the Tōkai, Kantō, and Okuu regions, the era name was changed from Meiwa to An'ei.
== Births == * In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1638]] [[:en:January 1|January 1]]) – Emperor Gosei, the 111th Emperor of Japan, was born (died [[1685]]). * In the 4th year of the Jōkyō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1687]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Akizuki Tanetoshi, the 5th lord of the Takanabe Domain, was born (died [[1753]]). * In the 1st year of the Ansei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1855]] [[:en:January 4|January 4]]) – Okabe Nagasada, the 13th lord of the Kishiwada Domain as well as a diplomat and politician, was born (died [[1925]]). * In the 1st year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:December 29|December 29]]) – Kitamura Tōdoku, a poet and playwright, was born (died [[1894]]).
== Deaths == * In the 5th year of the Eishō era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1508]] [[:en:December 8|December 8]]) – Shibata Yoshimitsu, a senior retainer (kanrei) (born [[1435]]). * In the 4th year of the Enpō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1676]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Tōdō Takatsugu, the lord of the Tsuno Domain, died (born [[1602]]). * In the 9th year of the An'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1780]] [[:en:December 11|December 11]]) – Miura Shuyora, a haiku poet, died (born [[1729]]). * In the 5th year of the Ansei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1858]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Gesshō, a monk, died (born [[1813]]).
