== Events == * In the 2nd year of the Jōō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1654|1654]] [[:en:January 4|January 4]]) – The excavation of the Tamagawa aqueduct was completed, with final completion in June of the following year. * In the 4th year of the Enkyō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1747|1747]] [[:en:December 17|December 17]]) – At a performance held in Osaka at the Takemoto theater, a collaborative puppet play titled “Yoshitsune Senbon Zakura” (a production by Takeda Izumo, Miyoshi Shōraku, and Namiki Chiryū) was staged for the first time. * In the 1st year of the An'ei era / 9th year of the Meiwa era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1772|1772]] [[:en:December 10|December 10]]) – Due to ominous signs including great wind and flooding in the Tōkai, Kantō, and Okuu regions, the era name was changed from Meiwa to An'ei.
== Births == * In the 14th year of the Kan'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1638|1638]] [[:en:January 1|January 1]]) – Emperor Gosei, the 111th Emperor of Japan, was born (died [[:en:1685|1685]]). * In the 4th year of the Jōkyō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1687|1687]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Akizuki Tanetoshi, the 5th lord of the Takanabe Domain, was born (died [[:en:1753|1753]]). * In the 1st year of the Ansei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1855]] [[:en:January 4|January 4]]) – Okabe Nagasada, the 13th lord of the Kishiwada Domain as well as a diplomat and politician, was born (died [[1925]]). * In the 1st year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:December 29|December 29]]) – Kitamura Tōdoku, a poet and playwright, was born (died [[1894]]).
== Deaths == * In the 5th year of the Eishō era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1508|1508]] [[:en:December 8|December 8]]) – Shibata Yoshimitsu, a senior retainer (kanrei) (born [[:en:1435|1435]]). * In the 4th year of the Enpō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1676|1676]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Tōdō Takatsugu, the lord of the Tsuno Domain, died (born [[:en:1602|1602]]). * In the 9th year of the An'ei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1780]] [[:en:December 11|December 11]]) – Miura Shuyora, a haiku poet, died (born [[:en:1729|1729]]). * In the 5th year of the Ansei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1858]] [[:en:December 20|December 20]]) – Gesshō, a monk, died (born [[1813]]).
